14:47.251 --> 14:48.585
Wait a minute.

14:48.653 --> 14:53.057
The hand in the pan of warm
water a stupid camp game?

14:53.125 --> 14:55.926
I don't even know who you are,
Sam Malone.

14:55.994 --> 14:58.028
I'm serious.

14:58.029 --> 14:59.763
Remember the last time
he got this upset?

14:59.764 --> 15:01.565
He ended up on a ledge.

15:01.633 --> 15:03.667
Yeah, you're right about that.

15:03.668 --> 15:05.052
All I'm saying is maybe he
shouldn't be alone.

15:05.053 --> 15:06.420
Yeah, yeah, maybe

15:06.421 --> 15:08.772
we ought to go over there with
some chips and a pizza.

15:08.773 --> 15:10.207
Thank you.

15:10.274 --> 15:13.410
Yeah. I'll get some videos
or something, right?

15:13.411 --> 15:15.746
Well, yeah, it feels good
to do something nice

15:15.747 --> 15:17.147
for somebody sometimes, yeah?

15:17.148 --> 15:18.482
Yeah.
This is Cheers, right?

15:18.483 --> 15:19.863
We, we stick with each other.

15:19.864 --> 15:21.952
NORM:
That's right. We take care of our own.

15:21.953 --> 15:23.587
Hey, guys,
you'd better take an umbrella.

15:23.588 --> 15:24.668
It's starting to mist.

15:24.722 --> 15:27.975
Mist?

15:28.043 --> 15:29.409
Oh, man, that, uh,

15:29.477 --> 15:33.130
that really messes up my hair.

15:33.131 --> 15:34.465
It's not gonna help the tickle

15:34.466 --> 15:35.999
in the back
of my throat either.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.685
And this, uh, sweater
is sure to pill.

15:38.753 --> 15:41.455
Well, now what are we gonna do?

15:43.841 --> 15:45.993
I'll get the pan.
You heat up the water.

15:58.807 --> 16:02.043
Now, Rebecca, you're,
you're sure you're okay with this?

16:02.044 --> 16:03.811
Because I wouldn't want
to do anything

16:03.812 --> 16:05.813
to compromise our friendship,

16:05.881 --> 16:08.549
and I know you're in a very
delicate state right now.

16:08.616 --> 16:10.051
You ready to hit the sack?

16:10.118 --> 16:11.802
Right upstairs.

16:14.422 --> 16:16.123
You get some champagne

16:16.124 --> 16:17.791
and I'll go upstairs
and get ready.

16:17.792 --> 16:19.159
Right. Okay.

16:19.227 --> 16:21.195
Take your time.

16:21.262 --> 16:23.030
This is not a drill.

16:27.836 --> 16:29.486
This is not a drill!

16:32.506 --> 16:34.407
(humming)

16:37.728 --> 16:39.046
(doorbell rings)

16:39.113 --> 16:40.497
Damn!

16:45.336 --> 16:46.686
Hey!
There you are!

16:46.754 --> 16:48.144
(laughs) I didn't want you

16:48.156 --> 16:50.891
to be alone and depressed
on a night like this.

16:50.959 --> 16:53.260
So what I did was
I brought over

16:53.261 --> 16:54.962
some Three Stooges
tapes we can watch.

16:54.963 --> 16:57.564
Whoo! Gloomy in here.
There you go!

16:57.631 --> 16:59.132
Listen, Sam, uh...

16:59.200 --> 17:00.734
Yeah, I know, I know, I know.

17:00.801 --> 17:03.988
My hair's all frizzy.
But what the heck?

17:03.989 --> 17:04.988
You're worth it, buddy.

17:04.989 --> 17:06.290
Sam...

17:06.290 --> 17:08.391
You know, I was thinking
about not coming here.

17:08.392 --> 17:10.644
Then I thought about how,
you know,

17:10.645 --> 17:12.880
how you'd feel to see
a friendly face around,

17:12.881 --> 17:13.881
so here I am.

17:13.882 --> 17:14.882
(both chuckle)

17:14.883 --> 17:17.117
Sam, uh...
Yeah?

17:17.184 --> 17:21.121
I, I appreciate all
this, but, you know,

17:21.188 --> 17:23.490
that you're here in
my hour of need and all,

17:23.558 --> 17:24.958
and I just want to tell you

17:25.026 --> 17:26.492
I think I'm okay with it now.

17:26.560 --> 17:28.995
I think I'm just
gonna head upstairs

17:29.063 --> 17:30.564
and you know... (yawns)

17:30.632 --> 17:32.132
put my head down, you know?

17:32.199 --> 17:33.667
I, I...

17:33.668 --> 17:34.735
Hi, Fras.

17:34.736 --> 17:36.002
Carla!
Hey!

17:36.070 --> 17:38.600
Oh, Fras, sorry about your wife,
blah, blah, blah.

17:38.606 --> 17:40.808
Well, brought some pizza.

17:40.875 --> 17:43.560
I'm just gonna dig right in.

17:43.561 --> 17:45.228
Give me a piece, there,
will you?

17:45.229 --> 17:48.916
Uh, Sam, this is such
a wonderful gesture.

17:48.984 --> 17:50.584
It shows a sensitivity that I...

17:50.652 --> 17:52.486
(Sam and Carla laugh)

17:52.553 --> 17:56.857
Geez, doesn't that
hurt Curly's nose?

17:56.925 --> 17:58.525
Well, of course it does.

17:58.593 --> 18:00.694
That's what makes it funny.

18:00.762 --> 18:01.962
(laughs)

18:03.798 --> 18:05.766
Nyuk-nyuk-nyuk-nyuk.

18:05.767 --> 18:06.834
Woo-oo-oo-oo!
Woo-oo-oo-oo!

18:06.835 --> 18:08.769
You got anything
to wash this down with?

18:08.770 --> 18:10.070
Yeah. How about
some napkins?

18:10.071 --> 18:12.006
Um, sure.
I'll, I'll get some.

18:12.007 --> 18:13.140
They're, they're upstairs.

18:13.141 --> 18:14.675
That's where we keep them.

18:14.742 --> 18:19.546
I'll be, I'll be back in, oh,
15 minutes or so.

18:19.614 --> 18:21.515
(doorbell rings)

18:21.582 --> 18:23.834
Are you guys expecting anyone?

18:23.902 --> 18:25.652
Uh, yeah, Norm and Cliff.

18:30.091 --> 18:32.459
Aha! Tell him what
he's won, Bob!

18:32.527 --> 18:35.128
Whoa! Pizza!

18:35.129 --> 18:36.196
Beer.

18:36.197 --> 18:38.098
Norm, Norm brought beer! Well.

18:38.166 --> 18:40.867
No, no, no, I need a beer.
I'm a little thirsty.

18:40.935 --> 18:42.505
Sure.
I'll, uh, I'll get you one.

18:42.520 --> 18:44.054
It's, uh, it's upstairs.

18:44.122 --> 18:45.622
You keep your beer upstairs?

18:45.623 --> 18:46.857
Uh, yeah, in the bedroom.

18:46.858 --> 18:47.941
You, too?

18:50.245 --> 18:51.962
(doorbell rings)

18:54.365 --> 18:56.333
Paul! (chuckles)

18:56.401 --> 18:59.970
Are you, uh, alone or did you
bring some friends, Paul?

19:00.038 --> 19:05.309
What's that supposed to mean?

19:05.376 --> 19:07.677
Well...

19:07.745 --> 19:10.080
Nothing.

19:10.081 --> 19:11.148
Come on in.

19:11.149 --> 19:12.349
Thanks for cheering me up.

19:12.350 --> 19:14.017
I didn't come here
to cheer you up.

19:14.018 --> 19:15.752
I, I came to say something.

19:15.820 --> 19:19.139
Everybody, there's, there's
something I've got to say.

19:19.140 --> 19:20.741
Uh, Woody made some comments
earlier,

19:20.742 --> 19:23.577
and at first I was angry,
but then I got to thinking.

19:23.645 --> 19:25.275
I took a long hard
look at myself.

19:25.297 --> 19:28.782
I'm 45 years old, my mother's
dead, what am I waiting for?

19:28.850 --> 19:31.951
I, I guess what I'm trying
to say is "World..."

19:32.019 --> 19:34.454
Hey, Paul,

19:34.522 --> 19:36.623
this is Frasier's night.
Do you mind?

19:40.728 --> 19:43.863
You're right, Sammy.
I'm sorry.

19:48.153 --> 19:50.453
Is there any pizza left?

19:50.521 --> 19:52.139
I don't think so, Paul.

19:54.509 --> 19:57.978
Just, uh, make yourself
at home, Paul.

19:58.045 --> 20:00.514
Say, my God, is it
still raining outside?

20:00.582 --> 20:02.583
You know, I'm, I'm gonna
go upstairs

20:02.584 --> 20:03.817
and close those windows.

20:03.818 --> 20:05.386
Okay? I'll probably be
a little while.

20:05.387 --> 20:07.120
Oh, no, no!
Hold on!

20:07.188 --> 20:08.822
Whoa, no, you don't, buddy.

20:08.823 --> 20:11.357
You're not gonna go up there and
brood and be all alone by yourself.

20:11.358 --> 20:12.759
No way. No way.

20:12.827 --> 20:15.295
We're here to make sure
that you enjoy yourself.

20:15.362 --> 20:18.832
Well, then let me
go upstairs and close the windows!

20:18.900 --> 20:20.267
I beg of you!

20:20.268 --> 20:22.402
It's been a long time
since I've closed the windows!

20:22.403 --> 20:23.937
They're wide open!

20:24.124 --> 20:26.957
Don't you be silly, you big lug.

20:26.958 --> 20:28.292
Hey, look what we did here.

20:28.360 --> 20:30.660
We made a little space
for you on the sofa.

20:30.728 --> 20:32.579
Yeah, you can be the meat

20:32.647 --> 20:34.982
in our best friend sandwich.

20:35.049 --> 20:40.904
Hey, Fras, we got six hours
of The Stooges for you, man.

20:40.972 --> 20:43.657
Nyuk-nyuk-nyuk.

20:43.658 --> 20:45.075
Oh, God, look at that, fellows.

20:45.076 --> 20:47.777
You big lug,
you got a tear in your eye.

20:54.235 --> 20:55.401
FRASIER:
Okay, guys...

20:55.402 --> 20:56.603
SAM:
Take care, buddy.

20:56.604 --> 20:58.404
Thanks again.
Good night.

20:58.405 --> 20:59.472
CLIFF:
Nyuk-nyuk-nyuk.

20:59.473 --> 21:00.907
Yes, yes,
nyuk-nyuk-nyuk.

21:00.908 --> 21:02.575
SAM:
We'll watch these again some other time.

21:02.576 --> 21:04.026
Okay, bye-bye.
(door shuts)

21:04.078 --> 21:05.578
(quick footsteps on stairs)

21:20.928 --> 21:22.529
Oh, Frasier, I'm sorry.

21:22.596 --> 21:24.230
I must have fallen asleep.

21:24.298 --> 21:25.348
What time is it?

21:25.366 --> 21:27.167
Well, it's pretty late.

21:27.234 --> 21:31.371
Uh, I guess I'll go
downstairs and, uh, sleep on the couch.

21:31.438 --> 21:32.518
Maybe I should just go.

21:32.573 --> 21:35.909
No, no, you don't
have to go home.

21:35.977 --> 21:38.311
You don't have
to sleep on the couch.

21:40.915 --> 21:42.348
Just a second.

21:48.589 --> 21:51.125
(door opens, shuts)

21:51.192 --> 21:52.392
Frasier, what was that?

21:52.393 --> 21:53.494
What was what?

21:53.495 --> 21:56.130
I thought I heard a door slam.

21:56.131 --> 21:58.399
You don't think those guys
are back, do you?

21:58.400 --> 21:59.466
No, no impossible.

21:59.467 --> 22:00.734
I locked and dead bolted it.

22:00.735 --> 22:03.303
They'd need a key to get in.

22:03.371 --> 22:05.672
Now where were we?

22:09.828 --> 22:11.998
Let's make this a night
we'll never forget.

22:16.067 --> 22:17.534
(door opens)

22:23.224 --> 22:24.775
Frasier?

22:24.843 --> 22:27.060
Lilith!

22:29.997 --> 22:31.798
Rebecca?!

22:31.866 --> 22:34.451
Lilith.

22:38.940 --> 22:41.241
Am I the only one
who feels awkward here?

